definition: to send out/to show (one's feeling)/to issue/to develop/to make a bundle of money/classifier for gunshots (rounds)

sentences.english: I know my own strength, and I shall never be embarrassed again by his coming.
sentences.chinese: 這次我既然能夠應付，等他下次再來，我便不會發窘。

sentences.english: Don't feel embarrassed about being different from others in public.
sentences.chinese: 不要因爲你在公共場合的與衆不同而發窘。
那害羞的女孩很容易發窘。

sentences.english: The police asked some awkward questions about where the money had come from.
sentences.chinese: 警方對這筆錢的來路問了好幾個令人發窘的問題。

sentences.english: The booming telephone voice cut through his dilemma .
sentences.chinese: 電話中的宏亮嗓音容不得他兀自發窘。
